Indus program slicer
http://indus.projects.cis.ksu.edu/
"Java Program Slicer module" of Indus

Convenient download links:
http://projects.cis.ksu.edu/projects/indus/

I downloaded everything I could to ~/bin/share/indus/, namely
    Kaveri-0.6.0B.pdf
    docs-0.7.2.zip
    edu.ksu.cis.indus.kaveri-0.7.2.zip
    edu.ksu.cis.indus_0.7.2.1.zip
    examples-0.7.2.zip
    indus-0.7.2.jar
    indus-ug.pdf
    jibx-run.jar
    slicer-0.7.2.1.jar
    slicer-ug.pdf
    staticanalyses-0.7.2.1.jar
    staticanalyses-ug.pdf

The jar files only contain .class files.
docs-0.7.2.zip is Javadocs.

The license suggests this is provided in binary rather than source form.
The license says, "YOU AGREE NOT TO USE, COPY, MODIFY OR TRANSFER THE
Program OR Documentation OR ANY COPY, IN WHOLE OR IN PART."

Kaveri is the Eclipse plug-in

===========================================================================

This section about external jars is a waste, because file
edu.ksu.cis.indus_0.7.2.1.zip seems to contain all the required jar files!

